                <text x="200" y="245" text-anchor="middle" font-size="13">Inflammation</text>
                <line x1="200" y1="200" x2="200" y2="180" stroke="currentColor"/>

                <text x="35" y="135" font-size="13">Habits</text>
                <line x1="70" y1="130" x2="130" y2="130" stroke="currentColor"/>
            </svg>

            <figcaption>
                Most scalp issues stem from disruption to one or more balance factors rather
                than a single cause.
            </figcaption>
        </figure>

    </div>

    <section>
      <h2>How to Think About Scalp Care Day-to-Day</h2>

      <p>
        Effective scalp care is less about doing more and more about doing things
        thoughtfully.
      </p>

      <ul>
        <li>Cleansing based on scalp condition</li>
        <li>Purposeful oil usage</li>
        <li>Realistic expectations from massage</li>
        <li>Avoiding over-treatment</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <!-- VISUAL PLACEHOLDER: Do / Don’t scalp care habits
     Minimal icons or diagram, neutral tone -->
    <div class="visual-placeholder"></div>

    <section>
      <h2>A Balanced Formulation Philosophy</h2>

      <p>
        At Nexusario, scalp care is approached through balance — using chemistry
        functionally and incorporating natural ingredients where they add real
        value.
      </p>

      <p>
        The focus remains on stability, safety, and long-term scalp comfort
        rather than extremes.
      </p>

      <p>
        This approach reflects our broader philosophy on how products are formulated at
        <a href="/about/">Nexusario</a>.
        </p>

    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Closing Perspective</h2>

      <p>
        Healthy scalp care is not about trends or labels. It is about
        understanding how the scalp works and supporting it consistently over
        time.
      </p>
    </section>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>


